# [[protection]], [[safeguard]] (protection granted by any authority)
#: {{uxi|fr|Il est en la protection et '''sauvegarde''' du roi.|It is in the protection and '''safeguard''' of the king.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Il s'est placé sous la '''sauvegarde''' de la justice|He placed himself under the '''safeguard''' of justice.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=[[w:Michel Zévaco|Michel Zévaco]]|title=Le Capitan|trans-title=The Captain|year=1906|month=April|year_published=1907|publisher=Librairie Arthème Fayard|series=Le Livre populaire|seriesvolume=Number 31|text=De tous ces événements qui lui étaient arrivés, ce qui lui semblait surnager, c'était plus que jamais la nécessité urgente de se mettre sous la '''sauvegarde''' d'un tout-puissant protecteur comme Concini, maréchal d'Ancre.|translation=Of all these events that had happened to him, what seemed to stay afloat to him was more than ever the urgent need to put himself under the '''protection''' of an all-powerful protector like Concini, Marshal of Ancre.}}
# [[certificate]], protection (of the writing by which this protection is granted)
# {{lb|fr|figuratively}} protection, safeguard (a person or thing that serves as a guarantee and defence against a danger that one fears)
#: {{uxi|fr|Venez avec moi ; comme je redoute sa colère, vous serez ma '''sauvegarde'''.|Come with me; since I fear their wrath, you will be my '''protection'''.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Son obscurité lui servit de '''sauvegarde''' contre la proscription.|His obscurity served him as a '''safeguard''' against the proscription.}}
# {{lb|fr|computer science}} back-up, [[backup]], saving (action of keeping important information safe)
#: {{uxi|fr|Il a fait la '''sauvegarde''' de ses données comptables récentes.|He made the '''backup''' of his recent accounting data.}}
# {{lb|fr|computer science}} back-up, backup (the secure data themselves)
#: {{uxi|fr|Son ordinateur est tombé en panne, mais il a pu recharger sur le réseau la '''sauvegarde''' qu'il avait faite le mois dernier.|His computer has broken down, but he was able to reload the '''backup''' that he had made last month on the network.}}
# {{lb|fr|bookbinding}} protection sheet, waste sheet (strip of paper made to protect the endpapers of books during the bookbinding)
# {{lb|fr|navy}} [[chain]], safety line, [[tether]] (rope for holding something)
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Sauvegarde''' de gouvernail|Rudder '''chain'''|lit=Rudder '''safety line'''}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Sauvegarde''' d'aviron|Oar '''safety line'''}}
# {{lb|fr|astronautics}} range safety, [[safety]] (all the measures provided during the launch campaign or atmospheric re-entry of a spacecraft in order to ensure the safety of people and goods in terrestrial, maritime and airspaces)
# {{lb|fr|astronautics}} range safety, safety {{lb|fr|by extension}} (result of the measures of range safety)

